cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper deals with machine learning and data mining techniques applied to textual data for predicting future events. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of ontologies, which suggests a connection to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of machine learning techniques and data mining suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on predicting future events suggests a connection to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
